    {
      "type": "narration",
      "label": "Narration 2",
      "lines": [
        "Isaiah 53:4–6 — \"Surely He has borne our griefs\nAnd carried our sorrows;\nYet we esteemed Him stricken,\nSmitten by God, and afflicted.\nBut He was wounded for our transgressions,\nHe was bruised for our iniquities;\nThe chastisement for our peace was upon Him,\nAnd by His stripes we are healed.\nAll we like sheep have gone astray;\nWe have turned, every one, to his own way;\nAnd the Lord has laid on Him the iniquity of us all.\"",
        "Narrator 1: The prophets spoke of One who would come.",
        "Narrator 2: A servant who would suffer.",
        "Narrator 3: A Lamb who would bear the sin of the world.",
        "Narrator 1: Not by accident…",
        "Narrator 2: But by the eternal plan of God.",
        "ALL: He was pierced for our transgressions.\nHe was crushed for our iniquities."
      ]
    },
